result.execSummary:
The defendant Markettous R Kimble was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Court finds the defendant was under the age of 25 at the time of the offense, the charge is a Class I felony, society would not be harmed and the defendant would benefit by expungement.  Court will grant expungement upon successful completion of the terms of probation.

Sentencing proceeds.  State has complied with victim notification.  Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant.  
COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms, must provide a DNA specimen for testing and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  

COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE -  36  months with  12 days credit; INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -  18 months; EXTENDED SUPERVISION -  18  months.  COURT STAYS the sentence and places the defendant on probation for a period of  2 years.

Court finds defendant   IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and   IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-  Follow all rules of probation
-  Take all prescribed medication
-  Do not operate a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license
-  Remain in school or maintain full-time employment
-  Pay the costs, fees, assessments and surcharges during the term of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
-  Follow all rules of extended supervision
-  Take all prescribed medication
-  Do not operate a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license
-  Remain in school or maintain full-time employment
-  Pay the costs, fees, assessments and surcharges during the term of extended supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a specimen for DNA testing. (if not already done so)
-  if confinement served,   -  DOC to collect monetary sums/amounts at the rate of 25% of prison funds.

Appeal rights given.  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence, Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief, Pretrial Incarceration Credit and Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgment received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.
